TASK_SCHEMA_VERSION=3
TASK_ID=457
TASK_TITLE=Enforce reserved team isolation: only team-internal roles can dispatch to reserved workers
TASK_STATUS=pending_user_confirmation
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_CREATED_BY=boss
TASK_TEAM=W7
TASK_DESCRIPTION=Reserved teams/workers must be protected from outside dispatch. Currently any Taskmaster or Subtaskmaster can send work to any pane. We need enforcement so that: (1) Reserved teams cannot receive dispatch_task messages from outside their own team window. (2) Reserved workers within a team cannot be ordered by roles outside that team. (3) The enforcement should happen at the message/dispatch layer — likely in the hooks (on-pre-tool-use.sh for send-keys guards, or the messaging system). (4) A reserved team's Subtaskmaster is the only one who can assign work to its workers. The Taskmaster can still communicate with the Subtaskmaster but cannot directly command reserved workers. This is about respecting team boundaries and preventing resource hijacking.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W7: Enforce reserved team isolation at message/hook layer:done\n2:W7.1: Implement Subtaskmaster team-boundary guard + Coordinator reserved-team guard in on-pre-tool-use.sh:done\n3:W7.2: Add reservation check to doey_send_verified in doey-send.sh + run bash compat tests:done\n4:W7.2: Verify reserved team isolation guards work correctly — test all enforcement paths:done\n5:W7.1: RE-IMPLEMENT Subtaskmaster team-boundary + Coordinator reserved-team guards in on-pre-tool-use.sh:done\n6:W7.2: RE-IMPLEMENT reservation check in doey-send.sh _doey_send_precheck:done
TASK_TIMESTAMPS=created=1775748242
